Class V8Function

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Value
      • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Object
        • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Function
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Releasable

    public class V8Function
extends V8Object
    A V8Value that represents a JavaScript function. JavaScript functions cannot be created in Java, but can be returned as the result of invoking a JS script or JS Function.

      • twin

        public V8Function twin()
        Description copied from class: V8Value
        Creates a new Java object pointing at the same V8 Value as this. If the value is mutated (by adding new members or changing existing ones) then both the original and twin will be updated. Twins are .equal and .strict equals, but not == in Java. Twins must be released separately since they have their own native resources.
        Overrides:
        twin in class V8Object
        Returns:
        A new Java object pointing at the same V8 Value as this.

      • call

        public Object call(V8Object receiver,
          V8Array parameters)
        Invoke the JavaScript function on the current runtime.
        Parameters:
        receiver - The object on which to call the function on. The receiver will be mapped to 'this' in JavaScript. If receiver is null, then the V8 runtime will be used instead.
        parameters - The parameters passed to the JS Function.
        Returns:
        The result of JavaScript function.
